subject: Add POST code logs page
commitMessage:
Add POST code logs page

This page will be included in the Health section of the primary
navigation. The user will be able to export and download POST code
logs.

Signed-off-by: Sandeepa Singh <sandeepa.singh@ibm.com>

why the span? I think that can be removed

I left comments on your section divider component in https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/webui-vue/+/42506. We can use that component here with a bootstrap utility for margin instead of using a scoped style

The design has changed slightly, the 'Export all' button has moved below the divider and towards the extreme right. I have pushed the changes and removed the divider, which can be put back in place while doing the real time progress indicators. Hopefully we'll have a reusable divider component by then.
why not add margin top to the row below instead of creating an empty row?
Remove . at the end of the sentence

Do you think it will make it more readable if we set the name to use either kebab case or underscores?

all-post-code-logs.txt or all_post_code_logs.txt? It might be an even better experience if we appended a time stamp so that they would not have to worry about changing the file name or overwriting if they were to download more than one. 😊
It looks like we are using this same file naming for download and export. Should we provide a different name for export vs download since one includes additional details? :)

Can we change this to either let? If you do, you will have to declare it outside of the if block. The reason this works is because var is hoisted. My recommendation would be to move it to line 332 and move everything down.
